  <section id="about" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="panel">
        <h2 class="rule">About</h2>
        <p>
                    I discovered my passion for computers later in life, but once I began exploring, I quickly became fascinated by how technology works behind the scenes. What started with simply taking computers apart and rebuilding them grew into building custom PCs for friends and eventually running a small business assembling systems.

                    That curiosity expanded into experimenting with small form-factor computers like Raspberry Pi and Arduino. Over the years, I’ve built projects ranging from automated garden monitoring systems to remote hive surveillance with cameras for my beekeeping hobby. These experiences showed me how technology can bridge the gap between simple concepts and complex real-world applications.

                    My journey also led me into software and operating systems. From Windows and macOS to Linux distributions, I learned to install, configure, and maintain multiple environments. At one point, I even developed a lightweight custom operating system with preloaded, customizable shortcuts to streamline specific workflows.

                    Networking and cybersecurity soon followed. I explored how information flows across systems, and I trained myself on tools like Wireshark, Metasploit, and the Kali Linux suite. These tools helped me practice defending networks, analyzing signals, and strengthening security skills.

                    Naturally, this path led me into programming. Starting with HTML and CSS, I quickly picked up JavaScript and began creating responsive web pages and applications. Today, I continue to grow my skills with frameworks like Blazor, constantly seeking opportunities to blend front-end creativity with back-end logic.

                    At the core, I’ve always been a builder and a problem-solver. Whether it’s assembling hardware, coding applications, or securing networks, I approach challenges with persistence, curiosity, and a commitment to learning every single day.
        </p>
